Jobs at MonsantoFor those looking to make their mark on the world, few industries have more potential for great impact than agriculture. Beyond agriculture experts, plant scientists, communicators and more, we need people with technology-focused skills like software engineering and data analytics. If you’re ready to help create solutions that can impact the lives of billions, you’re ready for a Monsanto career. 



[unex_ce_basic_banner_landing layer-name="banner" layout="align-center-left" has_overlay="no-overlay" cutout_image="" cutout_image_filename="Upload Image" cutout_layout="align-bottom" id="content_21bx8tu6e" post_id="24" semplice_styles_background_color="transparent" semplice_styles_background_image="https://monsanto.com/app/uploads/2017/03/MONS09_5974_crop_nologo.jpg" semplice_styles_background_size="auto" semplice_styles_background_position="50% 0%" semplice_styles_background_repeat="no-repeat" semplice_styles_padding_top="0px" semplice_styles_padding_bottom="0px" semplice_styles_padding_left="0" semplice_styles_padding_right="0"]
Jobs at MonsantoFor those looking to make their mark on the world, few industries have more potential for great impact than agriculture. Beyond agriculture experts, plant scientists, communicators and more, we need people with technology-focused skills like software engineering and data analytics. If you’re ready to help create solutions that can impact the lives of billions, you’re ready for a Monsanto career.
[/ce_basic_banner_landing]






 Search

Why Work With Us?Monsanto is making investments not just in products and technology, but also people. We know that great ideas can come from anyone. Jobs at Monsanto require employees to apply themselves in ways they never thought possible, and in return become a part of something bigger.Benefits and RewardsMonsanto’s compensation and benefits philosophy is to provide competitive rewards to attract and retain the best talent. We’ve implemented an annual incentive program that is tied to the performance of the company, your team, and you. Our exact benefit plans vary around the globe, but employees typically receive health insurance, retirement, and other benefits that promote a work/life balance.Career Development and GrowthWe believe that to grow as a company, we must grow as individuals. Performance is measured and rewarded on an ongoing basis. Goal setting, coaching, and feedback are essential components of career growth at Monsanto. You’ll also find plenty of opportunities through a variety of technical, professional, and managerial seminars, conferences, and continuing education.CultureThe best way to describe our culture is team-oriented and entrepreneurial. Everyone is encouraged to do extraordinary things. New ideas are celebrated and different approaches are often sought after. By incorporating the latest in technology with your experience, your ideas can push the limits of agricultural technology and maybe even change the world.RecognitionMonsanto has received several awards recognizing innovation, leadership, and workplace satisfaction.FORTUNE Magazine: One of the World’s Most Admired CompaniesWBENC’s America’s Top Corporations: Women’s Business EnterprisesDigital Edge 50 AwardHuman Rights Campaign: 100% on Corporate Equality IndexVictory Media Military Friendly Employer: Silver StatusWorking Mother 100 Best Companies 


[unex_ce_careers_search layer-name="Search" id="content_cnsd9n0tq" post_id="24" semplice_styles_background_color="transparent" semplice_styles_background_image="" semplice_styles_background_size="auto" semplice_styles_background_position="50% 0%" semplice_styles_background_repeat="no-repeat" semplice_styles_padding_top="0px" semplice_styles_padding_bottom="0px" semplice_styles_padding_left="0" semplice_styles_padding_right="0"]
Why Work With Us?Monsanto is making investments not just in products and technology, but also people. We know that great ideas can come from anyone. Jobs at Monsanto require employees to apply themselves in ways they never thought possible, and in return become a part of something bigger.Benefits and RewardsMonsanto’s compensation and benefits philosophy is to provide competitive rewards to attract and retain the best talent. We’ve implemented an annual incentive program that is tied to the performance of the company, your team, and you. Our exact benefit plans vary around the globe, but employees typically receive health insurance, retirement, and other benefits that promote a work/life balance.Career Development and GrowthWe believe that to grow as a company, we must grow as individuals. Performance is measured and rewarded on an ongoing basis. Goal setting, coaching, and feedback are essential components of career growth at Monsanto. You’ll also find plenty of opportunities through a variety of technical, professional, and managerial seminars, conferences, and continuing education.CultureThe best way to describe our culture is team-oriented and entrepreneurial. Everyone is encouraged to do extraordinary things. New ideas are celebrated and different approaches are often sought after. By incorporating the latest in technology with your experience, your ideas can push the limits of agricultural technology and maybe even change the world.RecognitionMonsanto has received several awards recognizing innovation, leadership, and workplace satisfaction.FORTUNE Magazine: One of the World’s Most Admired CompaniesWBENC’s America’s Top Corporations: Women’s Business EnterprisesDigital Edge 50 AwardHuman Rights Campaign: 100% on Corporate Equality IndexVictory Media Military Friendly Employer: Silver StatusWorking Mother 100 Best Companies
[/ce_careers_search]







Inclusion and Diversity at MonsantoMaking agriculture more sustainable requires a wide range of ideas and resources. Our employees come from a variety of backgrounds and have diverse perspectives that allow them to thrive in Monsanto careers. We create an inclusive environment where employees of all genders, ethnicities, backgrounds, and orientations feel welcome and able to contribute.Learn More About Inclusion and Diversity 



[unex_ce_basic_banner_landing layer-name="diversity callout" layout="align-center-left" has_overlay="overlay" cutout_image="" cutout_image_filename="Upload Image" cutout_layout="align-bottom" id="content_hsmqifj07" post_id="24" semplice_styles_background_color="transparent" semplice_styles_background_image="https://monsanto.com/app/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6750_2_crop_3.jpg" semplice_styles_background_size="auto" semplice_styles_background_position="50% 0%" semplice_styles_background_repeat="no-repeat" semplice_styles_padding_top="0px" semplice_styles_padding_bottom="0px" semplice_styles_padding_left="0" semplice_styles_padding_right="0"]
Inclusion and Diversity at MonsantoMaking agriculture more sustainable requires a wide range of ideas and resources. Our employees come from a variety of backgrounds and have diverse perspectives that allow them to thrive in Monsanto careers. We create an inclusive environment where employees of all genders, ethnicities, backgrounds, and orientations feel welcome and able to contribute.Learn More About Inclusion and Diversity
[/ce_basic_banner_landing]








  Meet Tessa As global seed compliance manager, Tessa helps farmers access resources. We asked Tessa to explain why her work is important and how her work can impact global food security.Read More about Tessa 




