Bayer and Monsanto to Create a Global Leader in AgricultureIn September 2016, Monsanto signed a definitive merger agreement under which Bayer will acquire Monsanto. Through this deal, the companies look forward to accelerating much needed innovation, optimizing the tools farmers have to integrate solutions on their farms and expanding the offerings that will be available to growers through broad licensing in the years to come. From delivering new choices even faster to expanding current solutions, this combination will support growers in their efforts to be more productive, more profitable and more sustainable.ResourcesBayer and Monsanto to Create a Global Leader in AgricultureMonsanto Shareowners Approve Merger with BayerMerger Agreement 8KProxyOp-Ed: Here's Why Bayer-Monsanto Combo is Good For EveryoneLearn More Here: Advancing Together  




